    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Project Report on Industrial Safety System for Workers in Coal Mines</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Ranjay, Nikhil<br />Andani, Pawan<br />P, Pooja sachan</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Industrial Safety System<br />Workers in Coal Mines</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">1-May-2013 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Srm University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P6109</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">In any industry workers safety is a major concern to ensure the smooth running of the industry. In industries like mining having a fixed system for environment monitoring and safety surveillance is not possible because of the nature of the industry itself, where in the location of work keeps changing almost on a daily basis. Hence a wired or even a wireless fixed network is not a practical solution. Such a industry requires a monitoring solution that moves with the workers as and when then move to new locations.
This project proposes a novel solution for such requirements based on multi hop networking communications. In this project a portable battery operated low cost device will be constructed that could be integrated into any of the various safety items worn by miners like the helmets for example. This portable device has a short range communication module like a ZIGBEE transceiver, sensors and transducers that can monitor the presence of hazardous gases or chemical in the proximity of the worker. For emergency signaling and acknowledgement using a beeper and a button is also included.
Once such a device is provided to each of the personnel, the ZIGBEE transceivers in all of their devices can be used to establish a dynamic multi hop network that can carry information about the personnel safety and working conditions to a central monitoring station.
. At any point in time if a certain person come in contact with a poisonous gas the sensor will sense the concentration of the gas and relay a message over the multi hop network to the monitoring station. At the same time the beeper in the device is sounded in a certain pattern to alert the person of the poisonous nature of the gas.
When the monitoring station receives the information about the presence of a poisonous gas in a certain region, it dispatches a querying message to the concerned person asking for an acknowledgement to ascertain if they are okay. This is done by using the beeper on the device. The querying message from the monitoring station triggers the beeper and the worker has to press the button to confirm if he is okay. When the worker presses the button, the acknowledgement message is transmitted back to the monitoring station. Incase the person does not acknowledge the querying message then the monitoring station can initiate an emergency response procedure to help the persons</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/17425">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/17425</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/17097">ICE-2013</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
